            The next 4 days will determine whether Wenger stays. 78% of the fans were calling for him to go once his contract run out, that number has greatly increased. The 3-4-2-1 suits us, it is just we need an upgrade to Ramsey (the worst player today) and 2 CBs not to mention we need our 2 new signings to play instead of sitting on the bench for Welbeck, a player who has never been clinical, and Bellerin, a right sided player playing on the left to accommodate a player who wants to leave. I feel for Holding. He was terrible today but was so because he isn't anywhere near ready to play at this level and had to face a dynamic front 3. He is 21. He needs to play, but at the championship level for a season. We have had 3 poor performances already. It is early enough in the season that it can be rectified a la Chelsea last season but we need new signings and a new hard-arse attitude from Wenger so players are scared into doing their jobs. being a professional clearly isn't incentive enough.

          • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

            @vieri- It is easy to see why Alexis wants to leave although he is hardly blameless himself. Bellerin has been very good for most of his time as an Arsenal regular and if Chelsea can win the title with Moses as RWB then Hector is certainly good enough. Holding is only 21 and needs at least 1 season at a lower level, maybe 2 then a loan to a sub-European competition prem team under a renowned defensive manager- he will still only be 24. Being thrown in at the deep end when you aren't ready always results in performances such as today. Welbeck is industrious but limited, a good squad player but I agree not a starter in a title winning squad. Xhaka is a riddle. Has excellent long-range passing skills but poor short-range interchange or tackling ability. Really, he requires somebody with legs next to him to do a genuine box-to-box role because he is immobile. Looking at how well Goretzka can perform the exact role we require, I find it amazing we haven't put in a bid.
